snippet.textDisplay:
I love your videos so down to earth, hilarious and informative. I'm guessing since you look around the same age as me we are both milennials. Your videos inspire me to be more creative in the kitchen, I used your stuffed pork loin recipe as a starting point to elevate my cooking game and it turned out really well, I had no idea butcher sections in stores or even a local shop will cut things to standard and give you free twine for cooking, I asked they delivered and it was a hit with my family and its now going up on the "easy shit to cook I've conquered board" up there with easy shit like baked ziti and baked mac and cheese. I just discovered strictly dumpling and watched the epic episode of you and the holy god of food adam richman along with dumpling man devouring and drinking and it was so cool to see three professionals gushing over each other and commenting on delicious food. Your cookbook is on my wishlist and I know this might not be in your wheelhouse or your type of content but a basics with babish episode that included a couple easy casserole style dishes you could toss in an average baking dish in 30 mins. Like for my baked ziti, I just cook the pasta, brown the beef and add the tomato sauce and let it simmer for 10 minutes, place in the dish, cover with three types of cheese and bake for 30@ 350....I'm sure theres other super easy baking dish recipes im missing out on that are as tasty as baked ziti that dont involve nasty shit like tuna casserole. Either way you rock WARCRAFT FOOD WHEN???!?!??!?!?!?!? SO MANY RECIPES IN THE WARCRAFT UNIVERSE PLEASE DO GAMING FOOOD!!!!!! Happy new year!


Edit: To clarify you did an Apex Legends Recipe, come on man....I know that was to get views, but seriously? How many video games deserved a spotlight in cooking before another mainstream battle royale game? lol
